as superseded by the Norman form, which gave rise to an important surname. The family in question were earls of Pembroke in the 16th and 17th centuries; they included the poet  George Herbert . By the end of the Middle Ages <i>Herbert</i> was little used, although it remained a favourite with some families, notably the Saint Quintins of East Yorkshire. Its greater frequency in Britain from the 19th century onwards is due partly to the trend for the revival of medieval names of Germanic origin and partly to the trend for the transferred use of surnames."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Herbertus was born in 1045, in Vermandois, France. He had at least 1 son with Emma."},"et":{"1045–":"1045–Surnud","1060–Female":"1060–Surnud","1095–Male":"1095–Surnud","1045–Male":"1045–Surnud","1045":"1045","1095":"1095","1060":"1060","Abt. 1095":"umbes 1095","Vermandois, France":"Vermandois, Prantsusmaa","Penhros, Upper Gwent, Wales, United Kingdom":"Gwent, Wales, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1045–":"1045–Kuollut","1060–Female":"1060–Kuollut","1095–Male":"1095–Kuollut","1045–Male":"1045–Kuollut","1045":"1045","1095":"1095","1060":"1060","Abt. 1095":"noin 1095","Vermandois, France":"Vermandois, Ranska","Penhros, Upper Gwent, Wales, United Kingdom":"Gwent, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1045–":"1045–Décédé","1060–Female":"1060–Décédée","1095–Male":"1095–Décédé","1045–Male":"1045–Décédé","1045":"1045","1095":"1095","1060":"1060","Abt. 1095":"environ 1095","Vermandois, France":"Vermandois, France","Penhros, Upper Gwent, Wales, United Kingdom":"Gwent, Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Herbertus est né en 1045, à Vermandois, France. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Emma."},"de":{"1045–":"1045–Verstorben","1060–Female":"1060–Verstorben","1095–Male":"1095–Verstorben","1045–Male":"1045–Verstorben","1045":"1045","1095":"1095","1060":"1060","Abt. 1095":"um 1095","Vermandois, France":"Vermandois, Frankreich","Penhros, Upper Gwent, Wales, United Kingdom":"Gwent, Wales, United Kingdom","lifeSummary